node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Apple Hub on September 01, 2021 tagging @rendersbyian. May be an image of wrist watch and text.

node.text:
Nikkei Asia is reporting that the upcoming Apple Watch Series 7 has been delayed due to its "complicated design" and production has been "temporarily halted.” The new watch will have blood pressure measurement capabilities that have complicated the production. Apple will likely announce the new Apple Watch at the upcoming September event, however, they may launch it at a later date. Render from @rendersbyian 

#Apple #AppleWatch #Series7 #Tech #AppleHub

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Apple Hub on August 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Apple Event expected on September 14 @theapplehub Apple'.

node.text:
Apple will likely announce the new iPhone 13 series and Apple Watch Series 7 at an Apple Event on September 14th and should be made official next week. It was speculated that the event could have been on September 7th, however, an announcement would have had to have been made today, making September 14th the likely candidate.

#Apple #iPhone13 #iPhone13Pro #AirPods #AppleWatch #AppleEvent #Tech #AppleHub

node.text:
Bloomberg’s Mark Gurman believes Apple CEO Tim Cook could leave the company as early as 2025 as he has a pay deal that runs out that year. The belief at Apple is that Cook wants to stick around to launch one more major product category, which could be the Apple AR glasses.

#Apple #TimCook #Tech #AppleHub

node.text:
According to analyst Ming-Chi Kuo, the upcoming iPhone 13 series will feature low earth orbit (LEO) satellite communication connectivity, which will allow users to make calls and send messages when cell signal is not available. The new iPhone will utilize a custom version of the Qualcomm X60 baseband modem chip with support for communications over satellite.

#Apple #iPhone13 #iPhone12S #Tech #AppleHub

node.text:
According to Jon Prosser, Apple is testing new iPhone 13 Face ID hardware that works with masks and foggy glasses. The render in the image depicts the prototype case used internally at Apple. It’s not clear if the feature will be ready when the new iPhone launches as tests were conducted recently, however, it could be released later as part of a software update. #Apple #Mac #MacBookPro #Tech #AppleHub
